25:
Awaiting return of ball.
Nephtim wants to keep playing.
29:
I think it's time for a break.
Papa Light's looking pretty tired.
33:
What?! No, I can go on. No matter what
world I'm in or what form I take,
I am a champion!
45:
Hey, Nephtim. If you're looking for
something to do, want to come
shopping with me?
52: If you promise to brush your teeth.
62:
Hm... We've got tomatoes and chicken
and ginger... Think that's it.
65: Deducing... Dinner will be red soup.
69:
Yep. Chicken and tomato stew.
You're sharp as a tack, detective.
72:
You have forgotten the pumpkin.
Stella's favorite part.
76:
You're right! Thanks, Nephtim.
Let me go grab one real quick.
103:
This is not the full extent of my abilities.
Observe.
114:
Sorry!
That took longer than expect... ed....
123:
Nephtim is the bee's knees.
And the cat's pajamas.
127:
Okay, who's been teaching you weird
slang?!
130:
Don't forget the fox's socks!
Man, I've never seen moves like yours!
132:
A star like you shouldn't be out here
performing on the streets! What do you
say to joining my troupe?
139:
Whoa, now hold your horses! That's
enough excitement for one day. Show's
overgo back to where you were!
144:
Phew... Finally got rid of that crowd.
You ready to head back, Nephtim?
160:
Play catch with your companions.
It will bring you closer.
165: Didn't that ball mean a lot to you?
169:
Playing catch has already brought us
together. It will now do the same for the
girl and her friends.
171: ...I wanted to do it. I wanted to "give."
174:
You're a good person, Nephtim...
Now let's go home, okay?
I need to get dinner on the stove!
181:
She's grown...
It brings me joy, as well as sorrow.
190: You have come a long way, Nephtim.
197: What do you think you're doin'?
201:
Performing acts of selflessness drains
high amounts of energy. Consuming
protein restores energy.
203:
It is therefore necessary that Nephtim's
carrots be exchanged for your chicken.
213:
Carrots are to be feared. And at times...
so is Stella.
